<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know Pullenvale and the western acreage corridor well. Selling acreage is a different discipline to selling suburban residential. The buyer pool is smaller, the qualification more rigorous and the campaign needs to communicate the lifestyle of the property as much as the dwelling itself. Photography, video and the way a property is opened to inspection all matter more here than in conventional suburbs.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The Pullenvale State School catchment is well regarded and is a consistent driver for family-buyer interest. Brookfield Road and Grandview Road carry premium aspirations among local buyers, while the streets running off Pullen Road into the bushland reserves attract buyers who prioritise privacy and seclusion. Homes with usable level land, established gardens and quality outbuildings, including stables and machinery sheds, consistently sit at the upper end of suburb values.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#191817; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Pullenvale Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Western Acreage Brisbane</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#191817; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Premium Rural-Residential</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Equestrian, family and lifestyle buyers</p>
